CatDescriptText: Mrs. Patricia King, 203 Devilliers St. was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 26, 1957, pg. 4, with question: "Do you believe we should have a state law forbidding strikes of trolley cars, buses, and taxicabs?" answer reads: "I couldn't say whether or not there should be such a state law. I work and belong to a union.  Therefore, I know how important a strike can be in order to obtain raises and other benefits."
